5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to Class 2 municipalities; to further provide
10 for the powers of certain industrial development boards.
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
12 Section 1. (a) For the purposes of this section, the
13 following terms have the following meanings:
14 (1) AUTHORIZING MUNICIPALITY. A Class 2 municipality.
15 (2) DEVELOPMENT PROJECTS. Any interests in land,
16 buildings, structures, facilities, or other improvements and
17 any fixtures, machinery, equipment, furniture, or other
18 property of any nature whatsoever used on, in, or in
19 connection with any such land, interest in land, building,
20 structure, facility, or other improvement, all for the
21 essential public purpose of the development of trade,
22 commerce, industry, and employment opportunities in the
23 corporate limits of the authorizing municipality for any
24 industrial, commercial, business, office, parking, utility,
25 residential, including without limitation homes, apartments,
26 town houses, condominiums, hotels, and motels, or other use,
27 provided that a majority of the members of the board
28 determine, by a resolution duly adopted, that the development
Page 1

determine, by a resolution duly adopted, that the development
